						<summary>

						<p>Sōmasundarēśvaran temple, west base.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanachakravartti Vikramachōḻa Year 6.</hi></p>						

						<p>Very carelessly drafted. This record contains a decision of the <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> of Vayiramēghapuram alias Jananātanallūr in Tirunalūr-nāḍu in Ōymā-nāḍu, enjoining a brahmin who had the <hi rend="italic">kāṇi</hi> of the temple of Tirunandīśvaramuḍaiyār, to take charge of some land in the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāṉa</hi> of this God and arrange for the worship of Gods Āḷuḍaiyār and Chandraśēkharadēvar.</p>						

						</summary>
